Program: In Our Time
Title: Darwin: The Voyage of the Beagle
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00gbf2g
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 6 Jan 2009
To celebrate the 200th anniversary of the birth of Charles Darwin and the 150th anniversary of the publication of On the Origin of Species, Melvyn Bragg presents a series about Darwin's life and work.Darwin's expedition aboard the Beagle in December 1831 and how his work during the voyage influenced and provided evidence for his theories.Featuring contributions from Darwin biographer Jim Moore, Steve Jones, geneticist at University College London, David Norman, Fellow of Christ's College Cambridge and Jenny Clack, curator of the University. Show less